article.headline: Princeton 64, Lehigh 54
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Noah Savage scored 18 points and Luke Owings had 17 to lead Princeton to a 64-54 victory over Lehigh on Sunday. Kyle Neptune scored a career-high 22 points for Lehigh (1-3) and Jose Olivero added 10, while sophomore Brian White added eight points and eight rebounds. Princeton (1-1) used an 18-5 run in the first half to erase an early Lehigh lead and build a 28-16 lead at the half. Lehigh hit just five of 20 field goals in the half. The Mountain Hawks shot 71 percent for the second half, but Princeton took a 53-34 lead on a jumper by Owings with 4:57 remaining and led 60-43 with 1:08 to go, holding off a late Lehigh run that closed the gap to 10 points.
